9) GROQ FAILURE CASES

Reject immediately when:

response is empty

response is not JSON

JSON has extra keys

JSON misses required keys

approved is not boolean

confidence is outside 0..1

market_state not in allowed enum

setup_quality not in allowed enum

entry_zone invalid

stop_loss invalid

take_profit invalid

BUY structure invalid

SELL structure invalid

model changes direction

model suggests lot sizing

model suggests override of stop/target policy

==================================================
10) GROQ TEST CASES

Groq layer should pass these categories:

clear BUY trend continuation

clear SELL trend continuation

weak / borderline setup

trend conflict setup

poor RR setup

spread-wide execution context

range market

structure not confirmed

fake-good setup with insufficient room

Expected behavior:

approve only when evidence is aligned

reject when structure/risk/regime is weak

confidence must be realistic

output must stay inside strict schema every time

==================================================
11) FINAL LOCK

Groq is a decision assistant layer only.
Python remains the system authority.

Authority split:

Python owns:

schema

risk policy

direction lock

execution rules

fail-closed behavior

Groq owns:

setup interpretation

approve/reject opinion

concise technical reasoning

checkpoint summary

Final rule:
If Groq output is not exact and valid,
system must reject it automatically.
